<span>Saddle Mountain</span> News</h1>
        <p class="">Saddle Mountain Unified School District always has something new going on. Visit this page often to get updates on the special things we are doing.</p>
        
            <div class="pom-container">

<div class="newsItem">
<a name="statewidedirectives"></a>
	<div class="newstitle">Statewide COVID-19 Directives</div>
	<div class="newsbody"><div class=""><p class="">Please see our most recent <a href="https://tb2cdn.schoolwebmasters.com/accnt_235106/site_239912/Documents/April-3-2020-Parent-Letter.pdf" title="" alt="" target="_blank">letter to parents</a> regarding coronavirus school updates. This letter includes information concerning meals, school closures, online learning resources, and much more. Thank you!</p></div></div>
</div>
<div class="newsItem">
<a name="breakfastlunchservice"></a>
	<div class="newstitle">Free Breakfast and Lunch Service During the COVID-19 School Closure</div>
	<div class="newsbody"><div class=""><p class="">Saddle Mountain Unified School District is providing free breakfast and lunch service during the COVID-19 school closure. Breakfast and lunch will be available for drive-thru pick up on Monday through Friday from 9:00 to 11:00 a.m. and is free for anyone 18 years or younger starting on Tuesday, March 24. We will provide both breakfast and lunch at the same time for pick up. Initially, meals will be available at Ruth Fisher Middle School, Winters’ Well Elementary School, and Tartesso Elementary School, as well as the Belmont Dairy bus stop. Please <a href="https://tb2cdn.schoolwebmasters.com/accnt_235106/site_235107/Documents/Breakfast-and-Lunch-Service-During-COVID-19.pdf" title="" alt="" target="_blank">see our breakfast and lunch service flyer</a> for more information.</p></div></div>
</div>
<div class="newsItem">
<a name="checkoutprocedures"></a>
	<div class="newstitle">Check-Out Procedures</div>
	<div class="newsbody"><div class="">
<p class="">Student item pick up will begin on Tuesday, May 12. Each school will have designated drive-through areas so you can stay in your vehicle and maintain safe social distancing. Student item pick up is scheduled by last names. Please come on the day designated for the first letter of your last name between 8:00 and 11:00 a.m.</p>
<p class="">If you have any school property such as library books, textbooks, uniforms, or equipment, please return them at this time or at the date/time designated by your coach.</p>
<p class="">Please take a moment to <a href="https://tb2cdn.schoolwebmasters.com/accnt_235106/site_235107/Documents/Superintendent-Check-Out-Letter.pdf" title="" alt="" target="_blank">read Superintendent Dr. Paul Tighe's complete letter regarding our check-out procedures</a> for more information. </p>
<p class="">We sure miss our students! Please stay safe and follow precautions to stay healthy.</p>
</div></div>
</div>
